      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Euro sinks to record low as traders speculate central bankers will not intervene to prop up price; euro settles at 82.81 cents, down from 83.72 cents in New York trading; graph; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>EURO FALLS TO NEW LOW. The euro sank to a record as traders speculated that chances are fading that central banks will prop up the currency. In New York, the euro settled at 82.81 cents, down from 83.72 cents on Tuesday.</p>
      </block>
